1. Install Monero Software

Download Monero CLI from the official website.

Extract the files to your project directory.

Make the binaries globally accessible (optional):

Copy the extracted files (e.g., monerod, monero-wallet-cli, monero-wallet-rpc) to /usr/local/bin to run them globally without specifying the full path.

Without this step, you'll need to run commands from the extracted folder or provide the full path each time.

üåê 2. Start Downloading the Blockchain

Run this command to download the Monero blockchain to your local machine:

monerod --rpc-bind-ip 127.0.0.1 --rpc-bind-port 18081 \
--prune-blockchain \
--detach

Explanation:

--prune-blockchain ‚Üí Downloads a smaller version of the blockchain.

--detach ‚Üí Runs the process in the background.

‚è±Ô∏è Wait for the sync to complete. It may take several hours or a full day depending on your connection.

üîç Check Sync Status:

curl --http1.1 -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18081/json_rpc \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
--data '{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "0",
    "method": "get_info"
}'
// live update
tail -f ~/.bitmonero/bitmonero.log


Look for:

height ‚Üí Current block height.

target_height ‚Üí The total height to reach.

synchronized ‚Üí Will change to true when complete.

üí° Note: You cannot monitor the progress until the RPC server is running.

üîë 3. Create a New Wallet

Run this command to generate a wallet file:

monero-wallet-cli --generate-new-wallet ./monero_service/wallets/monero_main_wallet \
--password "peter" \
--daemon-address 127.0.0.1:18081

This command:

Creates a wallet file at ./monero_service/wallets/monero_main_wallet.

Sets the wallet password to peter.

üîí The wallet password is stored permanently.

‚ö†Ô∏è Important: The RPC login credentials (e.g., peter:peter) are temporary and can be changed anytime. However, the wallet password remains the same and is required whenever you access the wallet.

‚öôÔ∏è 4. Start the Wallet RPC Server

Method 1: With Authentication (Recommended)

monero-wallet-rpc --wallet-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero_main_wallet \
--password "peter" \
--rpc-bind-port 18083 \
--rpc-login peter:peter \
--daemon-address 127.0.0.1:18081 \
--log-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero-wallet-rpc.log \
--detach

Explanation:

--rpc-login peter:peter ‚Üí Sets temporary RPC credentials (can be any string, but must match the Python script).

--daemon-address 127.0.0.1:18081 ‚Üí Connects to the local daemon.

--detach ‚Üí Runs the process in the background.

Method 2: Without Authentication (Local Testing Only)

monero-wallet-rpc --wallet-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero_main_wallet \
--password "peter" \
--rpc-bind-port 18082 \
--disable-rpc-login \
--daemon-address 127.0.0.1:18081 \
--log-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero-wallet-rpc.log \
--detach

Note:

Avoid using this method on a public network for security reasons.

üí∞ 5. Interact with the Wallet

Check Balance:

curl --digest -u peter:peter --http1.1 -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18083/json_rpc \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
--data '{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "0",
    "method": "get_balance"
}'

Get Primary Address:

curl --digest -u peter:peter --http1.1 -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18083/json_rpc \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
--data '{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "0",
    "method": "get_address",
    "params": {
        "account_index": 0
    }
}'

üîç Verify Blockchain Sync Again:

curl --digest -u peter:peter --http1.1 -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18081/json_rpc \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
--data '{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "0",
    "method": "get_info"
}'

Wait until:

height = target_height

synchronized ‚Üí true

üî¥ 6. Stop the Services

Stop the Wallet RPC Server:

monero-wallet-rpc stop_wallet

Stop the Monero Daemon:

monerod exit

üöÄ Next Startup Steps (No Full Download Required)

Once the blockchain has been fully downloaded, starting it again is simple:

monerod --rpc-bind-ip 127.0.0.1 --rpc-bind-port 18081 --detach

And for the wallet:

monero-wallet-rpc --wallet-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero_main_wallet \
--password "peter" \
--rpc-bind-port 18082 \
--rpc-login peter:peter \
--daemon-address 127.0.0.1:18081 \
--log-file ./monero_service/wallets/monero-wallet-rpc.log \
--detach





